        },
        "question_QNAbMN": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "2. I’ve tried retinol before and it irritated my skin. Will this?",
            "answer": "<p>Many retinol products are too strong for barrier-compromised mature skin. Our Vitamin A step is introduced in a structured way and supported with lipid repair to minimise irritation. The protocol is layered to support tolerance, not overwhelm the skin.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_axKJUH": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "3. Is this medical grade skincare?",
            "answer": "<p>The formulations were developed with over 40 years of clinical experience. The approach is grounded in skin physiology and long-term barrier health rather than cosmetic trends. We prioritise function over marketing claims.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_Xp66hK": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "4. How is this different from typical anti-ageing products?",
            "answer": "<p>Most anti-ageing lines focus on strong actives first. This protocol focuses on rebuilding the skin barrier first. Mature skin is thinner, less resilient and hormonally different. Treating it like 30-year-old skin often worsens dryness and irritation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_RXF4Tc": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "5. What results should I realistically expect?",
            "answer": "<p>Most women notice improved hydration, reduced sensitivity and smoother texture within several weeks when used consistently. Crepey appearance typically improves as barrier strength and lipid content are restored.</p><p>This is structured skin rehabilitation, not a quick cosmetic fix.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_TXFxpH": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "6. Do I need to use the full protocol?",
            "answer": "<p>For best results, yes. The products are designed to work in clinical order — Each step supports the next. Removing steps weakens the overall effect.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_WCHGdE": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "7. I’m not sure which products I need. What should I do?",
            "answer": "<p>Take the 2-minute skin quiz. It identifies your primary concern (ageing, dryness, reactivity, barrier damage) and guides you to the most appropriate protocol structure.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_RBpQgx": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "8. Is this designed for Australian conditions?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. The protocol was developed in Queensland and considers high UV exposure, dry climates and environmental stress common in Australia.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_BAa6tw": {
